emuInput.TitMainTitle: Joseph Diesner and Marie Diesner posed in front of Plymouth DeLuxe car, surrounded by baskets of flowers, with New Diamond Market and Winter's Bakery in background, another version
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 4, 1950, pg. 32, reads: "Given Car At Diamond Market - Mrs. Marie Diesner, 5424 Columbo Street, and her husband, Joseph, are shown at the Diamond Market, Diamond and Market Streets, Downtown, shortly after she was given the automobile shown above. Mrs. Diesner has purchased meat from the New Diamond Market for the past fifteen years, in fact, ever since she married. She was two children, Joseph, 8, and Patricia, 12.  Her husband is employed by Gulf Oil Research Department. - Harris Photo."
